Data development

Overview data for individual development

Metadata: - Etiqueta: a ID code of the individual - Imersion to Adulto: data stage was first recorded - Note data in Imersion to Adult represent dates and must be converted properly! - SP: species - Sexo: Sex - Temp: Temperature individual developed - Locality - ID: Is a full ID include etiqueta, temperature, species and locality - Days to change ontogenetic stage - L2_L1 means, Become stage L2 from stage L1 - L3_L2 means, Become stage L3 from stage L2 - Adulto_Imersion represent the total number of days from first immersion to adult stage - So on…

Development by stage

Piecewise model fitting

We created an acessory function to help validate all models with one hit

#   PIECEWISE MODEL FITTING

Stand_residout<-function(X){
 simul<-DHARMa::simulateResiduals(X)
    temp<-DHARMa::testResiduals(simul)
 out<-data.frame(
        Var=c("Uniformity(KS(D))","Dispersion","Outliers"),
            Stat=c(as.numeric(temp$uniformity[[1]]),
                as.numeric(temp$dispersion[[2]]),
                paste(as.numeric(temp$outliers[[1]]),"of",as.numeric(temp$outliers[[2]]))),
        p.value=c(temp$uniformity[[2]],
                temp$dispersion[[5]],
                paste(temp$outliers[[3]])))
return(out)}
